description.narrative: Children thrive in empowered and resilient families and communities engaged in transforming their social environments, norms and behaviours for increased survival, protection and development, which contributes to Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Health And Emergencies, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Polio Eradication. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: WCAR country programmes contribute to achieving the Strategic Plan 2014-2017 key results for children through application of country appropriate strategies - in development and humanitarian contexts
